                  </persName>
            . I am a Police-constable. On Saturday morning, the 16th of April, I met the prisoner in St. Giles, with a bundle - I asked what she had got; she said nothing but her own - I asked her to show me, but she refused; I looked, and found these articles, which were all claimed by the prosecutor.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. He left them with me for money.</p>
               <p>ROBERT CHALLIS. No, I did not; I had no other clothes to wear.</p>
